timeline/storyboard layout. Storyboard is generally considered to be easier for new editors, while the timeline is where more advanced edits take place. The software allows you to switch between the two modes with your edits intact. One of the best ways to learn the basics of video editing is to use storyboard mode to make the broad strokes to your project and switch to timeline mode to fine-tune your video.","The timeline module has 100 editing tracks. This allows you to create extremely complicated projects. Most users will never take full advantage of every editing track; however, if you’re ambitious, there’s nothing stopping you from editing a full-length feature film on your home computer. It wouldn&#39;t be &#34;The Avengers,&#34; but it might be something that could be accepted into an independent film festival."]},"id":"2beb8be2-aeee-4c24-a8cd-83c0b0a5fc3a","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Ease of Use"},"id":"2e41dfb5-10f2-418e-ab28-86a8c7a9c527","type":"heading"},{"data":{"path":"/ESrWmF4pjwRSbwonVEUBBZ.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"During our evaluation of the best DVD authoring software applications, we examined each product&#39;s interface to determine how easy it is to learn and use. Among other things, we tracked how complicated it is to perform common tasks, like performing basic video edits and picking and customizing menu templates, as well as burning a DVD and saving an ISO file. At the end of our testing, PowerDirector had the highest usability score of all the products on our side-by-side comparison matrix.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/57049-cyberlink-powerdirector16.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ESrWmF4pjwRSbwonVEUBBZ.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"ESrWmF4pjwRSbwonVEUBBZ","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ESrWmF4pjwRSbwonVEUBBZ.jpg","alt":""},"id":"82bca934-a71e-4419-bfbb-31a875a04afc","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Even though this sof